           SPELL=xfce4-minicmd-plugin
         VERSION=0.1.1
          SOURCE=$SPELL-$VERSION.tar.gz
SOURCE_DIRECTORY=$BUILD_DIRECTORY/$SPELL-$VERSION
   SOURCE_URL[0]=http://download.berlios.de/xfce-goodies/$SOURCE
        WEB_SITE=http://xfce-goodies.berlios.de
          MD5[0]=ddda19d051ee7a711b1be9b80ac6e288
      LICENSE[0]=GPL
         ENTERED=20030827
         UPDATED=20030827
      MAINTAINER=v.merkatz@gmx.net
           SHORT="A command entry box for the XFce4 panel"
cat << EOF
minicmd puts a small entry widget onto your panel. You can execute programs by
typing their names in the widget and hitting Enter or Ctrl+Enter. The latter
runs the command in a terminal.
It maintains history which is shared with xfrun4. This history can be accessed
by Up and Down keys.
EOF
